    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1349.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 456.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegraphic
                    instructions of March 28, 11 a.m., regarding the protection of the United States
                    consulate at Nuevo Laredo, I have the honor to advise the Department that I have
                    been informed by the Mexican foreign office that telegrams have been received
                    from the governor of the State of Tamaulipas and the chief of the military zone
                    in which Nuevo Laredo is situated stating that specific orders have been given
                    for <pb facs="0537" n="455" xml:id="pg_455"/> the protection of the consulate. I
                    am communicating the substance of this dispatch to the consul to-day.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
